    "created_at": "2016-02-06T02:55:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-02-06T02:55:38Z",
    "body": "I _think_ that systems often give you both \"yes\" and \"no\" flags, and the last one wins. So you can append to `CFLAGS` with `-fno-foo` and even if `-ffoo` appears before, it will work.\n\nMy brain may have also just entirely made this up.\n",
